   1 #!/usr/bin/env python
   2 # -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
   3 """pipreqs - Generate pip requirements.txt file based on imports
   4 
   5 Usage:
   6     pipreqs [options] [<path>]
   7 
   8 Arguments:
   9     <path>                The path to the directory containing the application
  10                           files for which a requirements file should be
  11                           generated (defaults to the current working
  12                           directory).
  13 
  14 Options:
  15     --use-local           Use ONLY local package info instead of querying PyPI.
  16     --pypi-server <url>   Use custom PyPi server.
  17     --proxy <url>         Use Proxy, parameter will be passed to requests
  18                           library. You can also just set the environments
  19                           parameter in your terminal:
  20                           $ export HTTP_PROXY="http://10.10.1.10:3128"
  21                           $ export HTTPS_PROXY="https://10.10.1.10:1080"
  22     --debug               Print debug information.
  23     --ignore <dirs>...    Ignore extra directories, each separated by a comma.
  24     --no-follow-links     Do not follow symbolic links in the project
  25     --encoding <charset>  Use encoding parameter for file open
  26     --savepath <file>     Save the list of requirements in the given file
  27     --print               Output the list of requirements in the standard
  28                           output.
  29     --force               Overwrite existing requirements.txt
  30     --diff <file>         Compare modules in requirements.txt to project
  31                           imports.
  32     --clean <file>        Clean up requirements.txt by removing modules
  33                           that are not imported in project.
  34     --no-pin              Omit version of output packages.
  35 """
  36 from __future__ import print_function, absolute_import
  37 from contextlib import contextmanager
  38 import os
  39 import sys
  40 import re
  41 import logging
  42 import codecs
  43 import ast
  44 import traceback
  45 from docopt import docopt
  46 import requests
  47 from yarg import json2package
  48 from yarg.exceptions import HTTPError
  49 
  50 from pipreqs import __version__

  52 REGEXP = [
  53     re.compile(r'^import (.+)$'),
  54     re.compile(r'^from ((?!\.+).*?) import (?:.*)$')
  55 ]
  56 
  57 if sys.version_info[0] > 2:
  58     open_func = open
  59     py2 = False
  60 else:
  61     open_func = codecs.open
  62     py2 = True
  63     py2_exclude = ["concurrent", "concurrent.futures"]
  64

  66 @contextmanager
  67 def _open(filename=None, mode='r'):
  68     """Open a file or ``sys.stdout`` depending on the provided filename.
  69 
  70     Args:
  71         filename (str): The path to the file that should be opened. If
  72             ``None`` or ``'-'``, ``sys.stdout`` or ``sys.stdin`` is
  73             returned depending on the desired mode. Defaults to ``None``.
  74         mode (str): The mode that should be used to open the file.
  75 
  76     Yields:
  77         A file handle.
  78 
  79     """
  80     if not filename or filename == '-':
  81         if not mode or 'r' in mode:
  82             file = sys.stdin
  83         elif 'w' in mode:
  84             file = sys.stdout
  85         else:
  86             raise ValueError('Invalid mode for file: {}'.format(mode))
  87     else:
  88         file = open(filename, mode)
  89 
  90     try:
  91         yield file
  92     finally:
  93         if file not in (sys.stdin, sys.stdout):
  94             file.close()
  95

  97 def get_all_imports(
  98         path, encoding=None, extra_ignore_dirs=None, follow_links=True):
  99     imports = set()
 100     raw_imports = set()
 101     candidates = []
 102     ignore_errors = False
 103     ignore_dirs = [".hg", ".svn", ".git", ".tox", "__pycache__", "env", "venv"]
 104 
 105     if extra_ignore_dirs:
 106         ignore_dirs_parsed = []
 107         for e in extra_ignore_dirs:
 108             ignore_dirs_parsed.append(os.path.basename(os.path.realpath(e)))
 109         ignore_dirs.extend(ignore_dirs_parsed)
 110 
 111     walk = os.walk(path, followlinks=follow_links)
 112     for root, dirs, files in walk:
 113         dirs[:] = [d for d in dirs if d not in ignore_dirs]
 114 
 115         candidates.append(os.path.basename(root))
 116         files = [fn for fn in files if os.path.splitext(fn)[1] == ".py"]
 117 
 118         candidates += [os.path.splitext(fn)[0] for fn in files]
 119         for file_name in files:
 120             file_name = os.path.join(root, file_name)
 121             with open_func(file_name, "r", encoding=encoding) as f:
 122                 contents = f.read()
 123             try:
 124                 tree = ast.parse(contents)
 125                 for node in ast.walk(tree):
 126                     if isinstance(node, ast.Import):
 127                         for subnode in node.names:
 128                             raw_imports.add(subnode.name)
 129                     elif isinstance(node, ast.ImportFrom):
 130                         raw_imports.add(node.module)
 131             except Exception as exc:
 132                 if ignore_errors:
 133                     traceback.print_exc(exc)
 134                     logging.warn("Failed on file: %s" % file_name)
 135                     continue
 136                 else:
 137                     logging.error("Failed on file: %s" % file_name)
 138                     raise exc
 139 
 140     # Clean up imports
 141     for name in [n for n in raw_imports if n]:
 142         # Sanity check: Name could have been None if the import
 143         # statement was as ``from . import X``
 144         # Cleanup: We only want to first part of the import.
 145         # Ex: from django.conf --> django.conf. But we only want django
 146         # as an import.
 147         cleaned_name, _, _ = name.partition('.')
 148         imports.add(cleaned_name)
 149 
 150     packages = imports - (set(candidates) & imports)
 151     logging.debug('Found packages: {0}'.format(packages))
 152 
 153     with open(join("stdlib"), "r") as f:
 154         data = {x.strip() for x in f}
 155 
 156     data = {x for x in data if x not in py2_exclude} if py2 else data
 157     return list(packages - data)
 158 
 159 
 160 def filter_line(l):
 161     return len(l) > 0 and l[0] != "#"
 162 
 163 
 164 def generate_requirements_file(path, imports):
 165     with _open(path, "w") as out_file:
 166         logging.debug('Writing {num} requirements: {imports} to {file}'.format(
 167             num=len(imports),
 168             file=path,
 169             imports=", ".join([x['name'] for x in imports])
 170         ))
 171         fmt = '{name}=={version}'
 172         out_file.write('\n'.join(
 173             fmt.format(**item) if item['version'] else '{name}'.format(**item)
 174             for item in imports) + '\n')
 175 
 176 
 177 def output_requirements(imports):
 178     generate_requirements_file('-', imports)
 179

 181 def get_imports_info(
 182         imports, pypi_server="https://pypi.python.org/pypi/", proxy=None):
 183     result = []
 184 
 185     for item in imports:
 186         try:
 187             response = requests.get(
 188                 "{0}{1}/json".format(pypi_server, item), proxies=proxy)
 189             if response.status_code == 200:
 190                 if hasattr(response.content, 'decode'):
 191                     data = json2package(response.content.decode())
 192                 else:
 193                     data = json2package(response.content)
 194             elif response.status_code >= 300:
 195                 raise HTTPError(status_code=response.status_code,
 196                                 reason=response.reason)
 197         except HTTPError:
 198             logging.debug(
 199                 'Package %s does not exist or network problems', item)
 200             continue
 201         result.append({'name': item, 'version': data.latest_release_id})
 202     return result

 205 def get_locally_installed_packages(encoding=None):
 206     packages = {}
 207     ignore = ["tests", "_tests", "egg", "EGG", "info"]
 208     for path in sys.path:
 209         for root, dirs, files in os.walk(path):
 210             for item in files:
 211                 if "top_level" in item:
 212                     item = os.path.join(root, item)
 213                     with open_func(item, "r", encoding=encoding) as f:
 214                         package = root.split(os.sep)[-1].split("-")
 215                         try:
 216                             package_import = f.read().strip().split("\n")
 217                         except:  # NOQA
 218                             # TODO: What errors do we intend to suppress here?
 219                             continue
 220                         for i_item in package_import:
 221                             if ((i_item not in ignore) and
 222                                     (package[0] not in ignore)):
 223                                 version = None
 224                                 if len(package) > 1:
 225                                     version = package[1].replace(
 226                                         ".dist", "").replace(".egg", "")
 227 
 228                                 packages[i_item] = {
 229                                     'version': version,
 230                                     'name': package[0]
 231                                 }
 232     return packages
 233 
 234 
 235 def get_import_local(imports, encoding=None):
 236     local = get_locally_installed_packages()
 237     result = []
 238     for item in imports:
 239         if item.lower() in local:
 240             result.append(local[item.lower()])
 241 
 242     # removing duplicates of package/version
 243     result_unique = [
 244         dict(t)
 245         for t in set([
 246             tuple(d.items()) for d in result
 247         ])
 248     ]
 249 
 250     return result_unique

 253 def get_pkg_names(pkgs):
 254     """Get PyPI package names from a list of imports.
 255 
 256     Args:
 257         pkgs (List[str]): List of import names.
 258 
 259     Returns:
 260         List[str]: The corresponding PyPI package names.
 261 
 262     """
 263     result = set()
 264     with open(join("mapping"), "r") as f:
 265         data = dict(x.strip().split(":") for x in f)
 266     for pkg in pkgs:
 267         # Look up the mapped requirement. If a mapping isn't found,
 268         # simply use the package name.
 269         result.add(data.get(pkg, pkg))
 270     # Return a sorted list for backward compatibility.
 271     return sorted(result, key=lambda s: s.lower())
 272 
 273 
 274 def get_name_without_alias(name):
 275     if "import " in name:
 276         match = REGEXP[0].match(name.strip())
 277         if match:
 278             name = match.groups(0)[0]
 279     return name.partition(' as ')[0].partition('.')[0].strip()

 282 def join(f):
 283     return os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), f)

 286 def parse_requirements(file_):
 287     """Parse a requirements formatted file.
 288 
 289     Traverse a string until a delimiter is detected, then split at said
 290     delimiter, get module name by element index, create a dict consisting of
 291     module:version, and add dict to list of parsed modules.
 292 
 293     Args:
 294         file_: File to parse.
 295 
 296     Raises:
 297         OSerror: If there's any issues accessing the file.
 298 
 299     Returns:
 300         tuple: The contents of the file, excluding comments.
 301     """
 302     modules = []
 303     # For the dependency identifier specification, see
 304     # https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0508/#complete-grammar
 305     delim = ["<", ">", "=", "!", "~"]
 306 
 307     try:
 308         f = open_func(file_, "r")
 309     except OSError:
 310         logging.error("Failed on file: {}".format(file_))
 311         raise
 312     else:
 313         try:
 314             data = [x.strip() for x in f.readlines() if x != "\n"]
 315         finally:
 316             f.close()
 317 
 318     data = [x for x in data if x[0].isalpha()]
 319 
 320     for x in data:
 321         # Check for modules w/o a specifier.
 322         if not any([y in x for y in delim]):
 323             modules.append({"name": x, "version": None})
 324         for y in x:
 325             if y in delim:
 326                 module = x.split(y)
 327                 module_name = module[0]
 328                 module_version = module[-1].replace("=", "")
 329                 module = {"name": module_name, "version": module_version}
 330 
 331                 if module not in modules:
 332                     modules.append(module)
 333 
 334                 break
 335 
 336     return modules
 337

 339 def compare_modules(file_, imports):
 340     """Compare modules in a file to imported modules in a project.
 341 
 342     Args:
 343         file_ (str): File to parse for modules to be compared.
 344         imports (tuple): Modules being imported in the project.
 345 
 346     Returns:
 347         tuple: The modules not imported in the project, but do exist in the
 348                specified file.
 349     """
 350     modules = parse_requirements(file_)
 351 
 352     imports = [imports[i]["name"] for i in range(len(imports))]
 353     modules = [modules[i]["name"] for i in range(len(modules))]
 354     modules_not_imported = set(modules) - set(imports)
 355 
 356     return modules_not_imported
 357 
 358 
 359 def diff(file_, imports):
 360     """Display the difference between modules in a file and imported modules."""  # NOQA
 361     modules_not_imported = compare_modules(file_, imports)
 362 
 363     logging.info(
 364         "The following modules are in {} but do not seem to be imported: "
 365         "{}".format(file_, ", ".join(x for x in modules_not_imported)))
 366 
 367 
 368 def clean(file_, imports):
 369     """Remove modules that aren't imported in project from file."""
 370     modules_not_imported = compare_modules(file_, imports)
 371     re_remove = re.compile("|".join(modules_not_imported))
 372     to_write = []
 373 
 374     try:
 375         f = open_func(file_, "r+")
 376     except OSError:
 377         logging.error("Failed on file: {}".format(file_))
 378         raise
 379     else:
 380         try:
 381             for i in f.readlines():
 382                 if re_remove.match(i) is None:
 383                     to_write.append(i)
 384             f.seek(0)
 385             f.truncate()
 386 
 387             for i in to_write:
 388                 f.write(i)
 389         finally:
 390             f.close()
 391 
 392     logging.info("Successfully cleaned up requirements in " + file_)
 393

 395 def init(args):
 396     encoding = args.get('--encoding')
 397     extra_ignore_dirs = args.get('--ignore')
 398     follow_links = not args.get('--no-follow-links')
 399     input_path = args['<path>']
 400     if input_path is None:
 401         input_path = os.path.abspath(os.curdir)
 402 
 403     if extra_ignore_dirs:
 404         extra_ignore_dirs = extra_ignore_dirs.split(',')
 405 
 406     candidates = get_all_imports(input_path,
 407                                  encoding=encoding,
 408                                  extra_ignore_dirs=extra_ignore_dirs,
 409                                  follow_links=follow_links)
 410     candidates = get_pkg_names(candidates)
 411     logging.debug("Found imports: " + ", ".join(candidates))
 412     pypi_server = "https://pypi.python.org/pypi/"
 413     proxy = None
 414     if args["--pypi-server"]:
 415         pypi_server = args["--pypi-server"]
 416 
 417     if args["--proxy"]:
 418         proxy = {'http': args["--proxy"], 'https': args["--proxy"]}
 419 
 420     if args["--use-local"]:
 421         logging.debug(
 422             "Getting package information ONLY from local installation.")
 423         imports = get_import_local(candidates, encoding=encoding)
 424     else:
 425         logging.debug("Getting packages information from Local/PyPI")
 426         local = get_import_local(candidates, encoding=encoding)
 427         # Get packages that were not found locally
 428         difference = [x for x in candidates
 429                       if x.lower() not in [z['name'].lower() for z in local]]
 430         imports = local + get_imports_info(difference,
 431                                            proxy=proxy,
 432                                            pypi_server=pypi_server)
 433 
 434     path = (args["--savepath"] if args["--savepath"] else
 435             os.path.join(input_path, "requirements.txt"))
 436 
 437     if args["--diff"]:
 438         diff(args["--diff"], imports)
 439         return
 440 
 441     if args["--clean"]:
 442         clean(args["--clean"], imports)
 443         return
 444 
 445     if (not args["--print"]
 446             and not args["--savepath"]
 447             and not args["--force"]
 448             and os.path.exists(path)):
 449         logging.warning("Requirements.txt already exists, "
 450                         "use --force to overwrite it")
 451         return
 452 
 453     if args.get('--no-pin'):
 454         imports = [{'name': item["name"], 'version': ''} for item in imports]
 455 
 456     if args["--print"]:
 457         output_requirements(imports)
 458         logging.info("Successfully output requirements")
 459     else:
 460         generate_requirements_file(path, imports)
 461         logging.info("Successfully saved requirements file in " + path)
 462 
 463 
 464 def main():  # pragma: no cover
 465     args = docopt(__doc__, version=__version__)
 466     log_level = logging.DEBUG if args['--debug'] else logging.INFO
 467     logging.basicConfig(level=log_level, format='%(levelname)s: %(message)s')
 468 
 469     try:
 470         init(args)
 471     except KeyboardInterrupt:
 472         sys.exit(0)
 473 
 474 
 475 if __name__ == '__main__':
 476     main()  # pragma: no cover
